<H2> <A NAME = NOW-section> NOW: Architecture and OS for a Network of Workstations</A> </H2>

<!WA8><A HREF="http://now.cs.berkeley.edu/">
NOW</A>: Network of Workstations as a High Performance Integrated System 
<P>
<h3> Areas of Research within the NOW Component</h3>

<UL>
<LI><!WA9><a HREF="http://now.cs.berkeley.edu/active_messages.html"> 
Active Messages:</a> Fast Communication Primitives (Culler)

<LI><!WA10><a HREF="http://now.cs.berkeley.edu/fastcomm.html"> 
Fast implementations of conventional communication layers.</a> Fast Sockets and MPI. (Culler,Anderson)

<LI><!WA11><a HREF="http://now.cs.berkeley.edu/glunix.html"> GLUnix:</a> Global management of resources. (Anderson)

<LI><!WA12><a HREF="http://now.cs.berkeley.edu/xfs.html"> xFS:</a> a distributed file system using striping across workstation disks and 
co-operative caching in client memories.(Anderson, Patterson)

<LI><!WA13><a HREF="http://now.cs.berkeley.edu/network-ram.html">
Network Virtual Memory.</a>(Patterson,Anderson,Culler)

<LI><!WA14><a HREF="http://now.cs.berkeley.edu/bench.html"> 
The NOW Benchmark Suite</a>(Patterson)
</UL>
	
<H2> <A NAME= Castle-section>Castle: Core parallel programming and language support</A> </H2>

<dt> <!WA15><a href="http://HTTP.CS.Berkeley.EDU/public/parallel/castle">The Castle Project:</a> Integrated
software support for parallel computing.
<P>

<H3> Areas of Research within the Castle component</H3>

<UL>
<li> <!WA16><A HREF="http://http.cs.berkeley.edu/public/parallel/castle/split-c">
Split-C</A>: A performance programming language for NOWs and parallel machines. Include <!WA17><A href="http://http.cs.berkeley.edu:80/public/parallel/castle/mantis/">Mantis</A> graphical debugger. (Culler,Yelick)

<li> <!WA18><A href="http://http.cs.berkeley.edu/public/parallel/castle/multipol/">
Multipol</a> a library of distributed data structures, designed to ease the programming of
"irregular" problems on large scale, distributed-memory multiprocessors. (Yelick)

<li> <!WA19><A href="http://www.netlib.org/scalapack/index.html">
ScaLAPACK:</a> Scalable version of the <!WA20><A href="http://www.netlib.org/lapack/>LAPACK</A> library of linear algebra routine for parallel computers. (Demmel,Kahan)

<LI> <A href="http://www.cs.berkeley.edu/~yelick/titanium/>Titanium:</A>
compiler and language support for parallel programming
of distributed memory multiprocessors(Aiken,Yelick,Graham)

<LI> <!WA21><A href="http://www.icsi.berkeley.edu/Sather"> pSather</a> is a parallel
version of the object oriented language Sather.(Feldman)
</UL>

